Interface LazyValues.PostCreateAction<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the objects to be created
    Enclosing class:
    LazyValues

    public static interface LazyValues.PostCreateAction<T>
    Defines an action to be executed after a lazy object creation.
    See Also:
    LazyValues.lazyNonNullValue(Supplier, PostCreateAction)

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void apply(T obj, boolean accepted)
      Called right after the lazily constructed object got created.

    • Method Detail

      • apply

        void apply(T obj,
           boolean accepted)
        Called right after the lazily constructed object got created. This method is called even if the object will be discarded. You can use this action for initialization and destruction as well.
        Parameters:
        obj - the lazily create object. This argument cannot be null.
        accepted - true if the object will be published, false if it will be discarded (and so it should destroyed)
